result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica Nicole Nusberger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Andrea recites the agreement.  State files an Amended Information with the Court.  State amends Ct. 1 and Ct. 2 to misdemeanor 948.122(3).  State files a Diversion Agreement with the Court for Ct. 1 & Ct. 2 in 16CF51.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.    Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  

DE pleads No Contest to the amended Ct 1 & Ct 2 in 16CF51.  Crt enters a No Contest plea on each count. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and stays the adjudication of guilt pending the full performance of the Diversion Agreement.  Court agrees with the Diversion Agreement and signs the Order.
